parameters: Chieftain: "Ugh, ugh... I'm truly... truly happy..."
Poso: "Damn it! Be happy, you hear!"
Kru: "It's true. He really looks happy."
Umi: "Chieftain! I will be happy! Thank you for everything until now!"
Umi: "I... never thought this day would come for me..."

Umi: "Yes... After being separated from Toto and Kaka, I was wandering in
the dark for so long... I was supported by Mii-A, the chieftain, and the
villagers, but somewhere inside, I thought maybe I wouldn't find
happiness..."

Umi: "But... while I was nursing you back to health... I suddenly had a
premonition... that you would become someone special to me..."

Kru: "Is that so? But you always seemed to have a frown between your
eyebrows..."

Umi: "Yes... I didn't know how to interact with you... It was the first
time I had felt this way... I even got scolded by Mii-A. But because Kru
was kind to me, before I knew it, I was smiling normally."

Umi: "Every day was so fun and enjoyable... I wished it could go on
forever. And then it really happened..."

Kru: "Umi... I also... always wished we could stay like this forever. And
then it came true."

Umi: "Yeah... Knowing our feelings are mutual makes my heart warm and fills
me with tenderness... Kru?"
Kru: "Ah... I will definitely make Umi happy!"
Kru: "Ah! More than anyone else... I love you, Umi."
Umi: "...I'm so happy... Kru... I also... I also love you, Kru..."
Umi: "Make a new promise with me..."
Umi: "Even when I become a wrinkled old lady?"
Umi: "Even if I eat too much meat and get fat and big?"
Kru: "No matter what happens, I will always love Umi..."
Umi: "Umi will also... always love Kru..."
Blessed by many people, we got married today.

At the feast, everyone poured drinks into our cups and reminisced about
Umi's past and the stories from when I arrived, making the atmosphere
lively. Everyone was genuinely happy for us, and I was so overwhelmed that
I cried several times.

Being united with Umi like this, being accepted by the villagers to this
extent, there's nothing more blissful. I don't know what led me here, but
from the bottom of my heart, I am grateful.
And as the banquet came to a close, we returned home...
